---
description: React + TypeScript + Tailwind rules for the Project Codex frontend.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/.{ts,tsx}", "frontend/.{ts,json}"]
alwaysApply: false
---
Frontend React Rules
TypeScript Strictness

tsconfig.json must have "strict": true — no exceptions
No any types — ever. Use unknown and narrow, or define a proper interface
All component props must be explicitly typed interfaces, not inline { prop: type }
Prefer interface over type for object shapes; use type for unions and aliases
All imports from '../types' — never redefine types locally that exist in types/index.ts

Component Structure
Every component file follows this order:
tsx// 1. Imports (external libs → internal components → hooks → types → utils)
// 2. Local types/interfaces (only if component-specific)
// 3. Component function (named export, not default for most)
// 4. Sub-components (if small and tightly coupled)
// 5. Default export at bottom
Use named exports for all components. Default export only for page-level components and lazy-loaded routes.
TanStack Query Conventions
Query key factory pattern — define in api/queryKeys.ts:
tsexport const queryKeys = {
  goals: () => ['goals'] as const,
  goal: (id: number) => ['goals', id] as const,
  tasks: (filters?: TaskFilters) => ['tasks', filters] as const,
  briefing: (date: string) => ['briefing', date] as const,
}

staleTime: goals/projects = 5 minutes, tasks = 2 minutes, briefing = 5 minutes, diary = 30 seconds
gcTime: 10 minutes for all
Mutations must invalidateQueries on success — never manually update cache except for optimistic updates
Optimistic updates only for: QuickLogBar submissions, Kanban drag-drop reorders, task checkbox toggles

Zustand Store Rules
Two stores only:

uiStore: active tab, open modal IDs, toast queue, drawer state, sidebar collapsed
canvasStore: viewport {x, y, zoom}, selected item IDs, drag state

Never put server data in Zustand — that belongs in TanStack Query cache.
Store shape must be typed with an explicit interface:
tsinterface UiStore {
  activeTab: TabId
  openModalId: string | null
  // ...
  setActiveTab: (tab: TabId) => void
  openModal: (id: string) => void
}
Tailwind Rules

Dark mode only for initial build — add dark class to <html> in index.html
Custom semantic colors defined in tailwind.config.ts under theme.extend.colors:

ts  'codex-bg': '#0f0f11',        // page background
  'codex-surface': '#1a1a1f',   // card background
  'codex-border': '#2a2a30',    // border color
  'codex-accent': '#6366f1',    // primary accent (indigo)
  'codex-muted': '#71717a',     // muted text

Use these semantic tokens, not raw Tailwind grays/indigos, for structural UI elements
Mobile-first: write base classes for mobile, md: for tablet, lg: for desktop
No inline styles except for dynamic values (canvas positions, user-defined colors)
No style={{ color: '...' }} for static colors — always a Tailwind class

Component-Specific Rules
KanbanBoard

Use @dnd-kit/core DndContext + @dnd-kit/sortable SortableContext per column
onDragEnd handler calls PATCH /api/tasks/reorder with fractional display_order
Wrap in React.memo — re-renders only when task list for that column changes
Column task lists derived via useMemo from the full tasks query

CanvasWorkspace

Transform state (x, y, zoom) lives in canvasStore — not component state
Pan via pointermove while pointerdown (not mouse events — supports touch)
Zoom via wheel event — clamp between 0.25 and 3.0
Sticky note positions updated optimistically on drag end, then synced via PATCH /api/tasks/:id/canvas
z-index managed in canvasStore — clicking a note brings it to front

QuickLogBar

Controlled input — useState for text, log type, linked project/task
On submit: optimistic update to diary query cache, then POST, then invalidate
Clear and refocus input immediately after submit (don't wait for server)
Keyboard: Enter submits, Escape clears, @ triggers project/task mention picker

Forms & Drawers

No <form> elements — use div with onClick handlers
TaskDrawer: slide up from bottom on mobile (translate-y transition), right panel on desktop
All drawers use AnimatePresence + motion.div from Framer Motion
Drawer backdrop click closes the drawer

Performance Rules

React.memo on: KanbanColumn, TaskCard, StickyNote, LogEntry
useMemo for: filtered/sorted task lists, canvas item transforms, chart data
useCallback for: drag handlers, form submit handlers passed as props
Lazy load page components with React.lazy + Suspense
Images (weather icons, avatar initials): always specify width and height

File Organization
api/          — one file per resource, typed return values
components/   — organized by feature domain (home/, productivity/, canvas/, diary/, ui/)
hooks/        — one hook per concern, prefixed with `use`
stores/       — uiStore.ts, canvasStore.ts only
types/        — index.ts only, never split
pages/        — one file per route
